    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-29T13:31:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-29T13:31:00-05:00" n="468"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">888.2553/5–2854: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 468<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Iran</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d468fn1">Repeated to London. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_SJH1">Stutesman</persName>, cleared with <persName
                            corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName>, and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_JJD1">Jernegan</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-29T14:31:00-04:00"
                            >May 29, 1954—2:31 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2337. Department considers it essential Shah have no doubt regarding firmness
                    United States support <persName corresp="#p_ZMF1">Zahedi</persName> and our deep
                    concern at indications Shah may be considering change government present time.
                    We fully endorse line you have taken with Shah and <persName corresp="#p_AH1"
                        >Ala</persName> (your telegram 2418 repeated London 733<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d468fn2">
                        <ref target="#d466">Document 466</ref>.</note>) and urge you use every means
                    maintain Shah’s cooperation with <persName corresp="#p_ZMF1">Zahedi</persName>
                    government.</p>
                <p>… <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName> gave opinion <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZMF1">Zahedi</persName> government prepared make oil agreement
                    while many Shah’s advisers such as <gloss target="#t_NIOC1">NIOC</gloss>
                    officials were reluctant and obstructionist in attitude. Serious risk therefore
                    if <persName corresp="#p_ZMF1">Zahedi</persName> government fell that new
                    government would be less willing make reasonable oil settlement and Shah’s
                    irresolution would continue. In this connection <persName corresp="#p_BHA1"
                        >Byroade</persName> made point that “make or break stage” seems to be
                    approaching when we must be prepared take strong line with Shah who is key to
                    Majlis acceptance agreement. It is particularly important therefore that United
                    States … give … firm advice to Shah at this stage.…</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
